    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hello!\r\nI'm using cython with cmake in my project. There are several solutions to determine pyx file dependencies. They all parse source files with regular expressions using cmake like that: https://github.com/scikit-build/scikit-build/blob/master/skbuild/resources/cmake/UseCython.cmake#L234 \r\n\r\nI'd like to implement it as distinct tool.\r\nCould it be useful to make cython compiler do this? Some kind of \"gcc -M\" behavior.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This could get implemented, sure. But in the end, generated dependency lists always get outdated.\r\n\r\nYou could also just blindly call `cythonize $(find -name \"*.pyx\")` and see which `.c` files it regenerates.",
